u not grimace, if a quote was deliberately taken out of context by a major and respected organization (CoE) in order to further an agenda by a politician. &#10;Please look at the Badman Report, down load it, and pay attention to the published CoE quote.&#10;Then go and read (link above) what the CoE told to the multi-party Select Committee. Does that make you not question the process? &#10;Tell me, yes/no, is this the way you want laws written in the UK?&#10;Or should the process start over fresh?"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="765" language="en" documentId="1030" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="MidlandsStewart" date="07 November 2009 1:36pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6754356" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="1030" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="22"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="23" end="270"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="271" end="434"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="435" end="528"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="529" end="659"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="660" end="725"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="726" end="765"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>